RESULTS: Twenty-five studies were included for final meta-analysis. Firefighters 
exhibited significantly lower mortality rate for heart disease (SMR = 0.64; 
95%CI: 0.51-0.80), cerebrovascular disease (SMR = 0.67; 95%CI: 0.50-0.90), 
diabetes mellitus (SMR = 0.48; 95%CI: 0.32-0.70), intentional self-harm/suicide 
(SMR = 0.52; 95%CI: 0.39-0.70), chronic lower respiratory disease (SMR = 0.71; 
95%CI: 0.55-0.91), and accidents/injuries (SMR = 0.77; 95%CI: 0.62-0.98)
